<p>I want to add items of my class <code>treeviewitem</code> to a TreeView.</p>  <p>And I want to bind the ItemSource of this TreeViewItem to a method of itself !</p>  <p>I am trying to use the ObjectDataProvider for this.. See my XAML:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;Grid Background="#FFE5E5E5"&gt;     &lt;Grid.Resources&gt;         &lt;HierarchicalDataTemplate DataType="{x:Type myNs:treeviewitem}"&gt;             &lt;HierarchicalDataTemplate.Resources&gt;                 &lt;ObjectDataProvider x:Key="getItems"                                     MethodName="GetItems"                                     ObjectInstance="{Binding RelativeSource={RelativeSource Self}}" /&gt;             &lt;/HierarchicalDataTemplate.Resources&gt;             &lt;HierarchicalDataTemplate.ItemsSource&gt;                 &lt;Binding Source="{StaticResource getItems}" /&gt;             &lt;/HierarchicalDataTemplate.ItemsSource&gt;             &lt;StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal"&gt;                 &lt;TextBlock Margin="5,0,0,0"                            Text="{Binding Name}" /&gt;             &lt;/StackPanel&gt;         &lt;/HierarchicalDataTemplate&gt;     &lt;/Grid.Resources&gt;     &lt;TreeView x:Name="guiTreeview"               HorizontalAlignment="Left"               Width="200" /&gt; &lt;/Grid&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But binding to an <code>ObjectInstance</code> isnt possible!</p>  <p>How is it possible to get the current object instance "into" the ObjectDataProvider?</p>  <p>What would be the right way of doint this?</p>  <p>And NO, its not possible to use a Property ..</p>